content.description:
The Poukachev Prow is a steep beautiful and tall basalt boulder problem.  Begin low, climb sculpted pockets and crimps.  Continue through insecure moves and stay on the prow to top it out. 

  It is pretty tall.....
content.location: Walk down canyon from where FR105 crosses Tule Tank Wash.  The Poukachev Prow is on the left side of the wash, probably 10-20 minutes walk from parking.  You can see it from the wash, but will need to walk up through some locust and trees to reach it.

content.description: Tule Tank Wash is a cool basalt canyon in the headwaters of Sycamore Canyon.  Good potential for bouldering and maybe short routes on basalt cliffbands.     It is a beautiful area, and a fun little adventure hike to cruise downstream through the basalt narrows.
